    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain your<strong> mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the<strong> drained mozzarella</strong> into small pieces and add them to a medium bowl with your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[2 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give it a good stir – this is your <strong>homemade stracciatella</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
