    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes have softened, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> to the pan with your <strong>sun-dried tomato pesto</strong>,<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>ground almonds</strong> and a very generous splash of <strong>starchy</strong> <strong>pasta water</strong></p><p>Cook for 30 secs or until fragrant, then add the <strong>drained spaghetti</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for a further 30 secs – this is your <strong>Trapanese-style pesto spaghetti</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy cooking water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
